name: WorksheetCollection
description: Represents a collection of worksheet objects that are part of the workbook.

info.title: Office JavaScript Add-in API
info.description: Office JavaScript Add-in API for June fork

methods.name: getActiveWorksheet
methods.description: Gets the currently active worksheet in the workbook.

methods.name: getItem
methods.description: Gets a worksheet object using its Name or ID.

parameters.name: index
parameters.description: The Name or ID of the worksheet.

methods.name: add
methods.description: Adds a new worksheet to the workbook. The worksheet will be added at the end of existing worksheets. If you wish to activate the newly added worksheet, call ".activate() on it.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the worksheet to be added. If specified, name should be unqiue. If not specified, Excel determines the name of the new worksheet.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
